🔹 What is REST API in Spring Boot?

👉 A REST API is a way for two systems to communicate over HTTP.

Client (Consumer) → sends request
Server (Provider) → sends response

Example:

Browser / Postman → Spring Boot App → Response
🔹 Why spring-boot-starter-web?

👉 This dependency provides:

Embedded server (Tomcat)
REST support
Jackson (JSON conversion)
DispatcherServlet
🔹 Important Annotations (Very Important 🔥)
1️⃣ @RestController

👉 Marks class as REST API

@RestController
public class MsgRestController { }

✔ Combines:

@Controller
@ResponseBody (returns JSON/text)
2️⃣ @GetMapping

👉 Used for GET request (read data)

@GetMapping("/welcome")
public String getWelcomeMsg() {
    return "Welcome to REST API..!!";
}

👉 URL:

http://localhost:8080/welcome
3️⃣ @RequestParam

👉 Used to read query parameters (key-value)

@GetMapping("/greet")
public String getGreetMsg(@RequestParam("name") String name) {
    return name + ", Good Morning..!!";
}

👉 URL:

http://localhost:8080/greet?name=Rishav

👉 Output:

Rishav, Good Morning..!!
4️⃣ @PathVariable

👉 Used to read values from URL path

@GetMapping("/user/{id}")
public String getUser(@PathVariable("id") int id) {
    return "User ID: " + id;
}

👉 URL:

/user/101
5️⃣ @RequestBody

👉 Used to read JSON data from request

@PostMapping("/user")
public String addUser(@RequestBody User user) {
    return "User Added: " + user.getName();
}

👉 Input (JSON):

{
  "name": "Rishav",
  "age": 22
}
🔹 HTTP Methods (Core Concept 🔥)
Method	Purpose
GET	Read data
POST	Create data
PUT	Update data
DELETE	Delete data
🔹 Important Notes (Very Important for Interview)
✅ 1. GET
No request body ❌
Only query/path params
✅ 2. POST / PUT / DELETE
Can have request body
Used to send JSON/XML
🔹 Request vs Response Body
👉 Request Body
Sent by client
Contains data (JSON)
👉 Response Body
Sent by server
Contains result (JSON/String)
🔹 How Flow Works (Important)
Client sends HTTP request
Spring Boot receives it
Controller method executes
Returns response
Jackson converts → JSON
Sent back to client
